theorem Topology.closure_eq_compl_interior_compl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    closure (A : Set X) = (interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ))ᶜ := by
  -- First, rewrite `interior (Aᶜ)` using the existing complement lemma.
  have h :
      interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) = (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
    simpa [Set.compl_compl] using
      (Topology.interior_eq_compl_closure_compl
        (X := X) (A := ((A : Set X)ᶜ)))
  -- Taking complements of both sides yields the desired statement.
  have h_compl :
      (interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ))ᶜ = closure (A : Set X) := by
    simpa using congrArg Set.compl h
  simpa [Set.compl_compl] using h_compl.symm

theorem Topology.interior_eq_compl_closure_compl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    interior (A : Set X) = (closure ((A : Set X)ᶜ))ᶜ := by
  -- Apply the lemma about the interior of a complement and simplify.
  simpa [compl_compl] using
    (interior_compl (s := (Aᶜ : Set X)))

theorem Topology.interior_compl_eq_compl_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (Aᶜ : Set X) = (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
  simpa using interior_compl (A := A)
